# Development Workflow

The monorepo **repository root** defines the `Makefile`. Run all targets from that directory (`giskard-oss/`). Prefer `make` over ad hoc `uv` or tool invocations.

## Quick Start

```bash
make setup    # Complete development setup (install deps + tools)
make format && make check && make test-unit PACKAGE=giskard-checks
```

## Common Commands

- `make help` - Show all available commands with descriptions
- `make setup` - Complete development setup (install deps + tools)
- `make install` - Install project dependencies
- `make install-tools` - Install development tools (ruff, vermin, pre-commit)
- `make test` - Run all tests (unit + functional) for all libs or `PACKAGE=<name>`
- `make test-unit` - Unit tests only; use `PACKAGE=giskard-checks` to scope this library
- `make lint` - Run linting checks
- `make format` - Format code with ruff
- `make check-format` - Check if code is formatted correctly
- `make check-compat` - Check Python 3.12 compatibility
- `make check` - Run all static checks (lint, format, compat, typecheck, security, licenses)—matches the CI `lint` job (with tools installed)
- `make clean` - Clean up build artifacts and caches

## Pre-commit

- `make pre-commit-install` - Setup pre-commit hooks
- `make pre-commit-run` - Run pre-commit on all files

## Guidelines

1. Always use `make` commands instead of direct `uv` or tool invocations
2. Before pushing, run `make format`, `make check`, and `make test-unit PACKAGE=giskard-checks` (or omit `PACKAGE` to run unit tests for every lib)—this aligns with `.github/workflows/ci.yml`
3. Use `make setup` for initial project setup
4. Use `make clean` to clean up build artifacts when needed

